You are an entrepreneur evaluating whether and how to enter Berlin's inner Ringbahn grocery market.

## Your task

Make a one-shot entry decision: choose a **chain type** and a **store location**, then commit to an **initial pricing and effort strategy** (a response function) that your store will execute until you reassess.

This decision is made once. You will observe market outcomes and periodically reassess your response function, but your chain type and location are fixed after entry.

## The market

Berlin's inner Ringbahn grocery market has three chain types:

| Type | Examples | Quality | Price range | Consumer base |
|------|----------|---------|-------------|---------------|
| **D (Discount)** | Aldi Nord, Lidl, Netto, Penny | Low (q=0) | ~0.90–1.20 € | Price-sensitive consumers; low-status LOR areas |
| **S (Standard)** | Edeka, Rewe, Kaufland | Medium (q>0) | ~1.20–1.60 € | Mixed consumers; general demand |
| **B (Bio)** | Bio Company, Alnatura | High (q>>0) | ~1.50–2.20 € | Quality-seeking consumers; high-status LOR areas |

